The '''Philadelphia Eagles''' [[American football]] club is a [[National Football League]] team based in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]]. The Eagles, along with the [[Pittsburgh Steelers]] and the [[Cincinnati Reds (NFL)|Cincinnati Reds]], joined the NFL as [[1933]] [[expansion team]]s. The team is regarded as a second incarnation of the defunct NFL team [[Frankford Yellow Jackets]], who folded two years earlier due to financial hardships brought on by the [[Great Depression]].
